{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/59944", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/59944/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/59944/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/59944/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/59944", "id": 432886924, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0MzI4ODY5MjQ=", "number": 59944, "title": "Memory leak when sending/receiving mpsc or crossbeam channel", "user": {"login": "pusateri", "id": 90469, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjkwNDY5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/90469?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/pusateri", "html_url": "https://github.com/pusateri", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pusateri/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pusateri/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pusateri/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pusateri/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pusateri/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pusateri/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pusateri/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pusateri/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pusateri/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 5, "created_at": "2019-04-13T19:01:30Z", "updated_at": "2022-09-13T09:59:01Z", "closed_at": "2019-04-13T19:11:44Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I may be doing something wrong but I was seeing a memory leak using both crossbeam and mpsc channels and so I created a simple loop program that replicates the leak. I would expect the message over the channel to be freed once it is received but the program memory grows without bound.\r\n\r\n% rustc --version\r\nrustc 1.34.0 (91856ed52 2019-04-10)\r\n% rustup toolchain list\r\nstable-x86_64-apple-darwin (default)\r\n```\r\nuse std::sync::mpsc::channel;\r\nuse std::thread;\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n\r\n    let (send, recv) = channel();\r\n\r\n    thread::spawn(move || {\r\n        for x in recv.iter() {\r\n            println!(\"Got: {}\", x);\r\n        }\r\n    });\r\n\r\n    let mut i = 0;\r\n    loop {\r\n        send.send(i).unwrap();\r\n        i += 1;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nHere's the crossbeam version too:\r\n```\r\nuse crossbeam_channel::unbounded;\r\nuse std::thread;\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n\r\n    let (send, recv) = unbounded();\r\n\r\n    thread::spawn(move || {\r\n        for x in recv.iter() {\r\n            println!(\"Got: {}\", x);\r\n        }\r\n    });\r\n\r\n    let mut i = 0;\r\n    loop {\r\n        send.send(i).unwrap();\r\n        i += 1;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "jonas-schievink", "id": 1786438, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE3ODY0Mzg=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1786438?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink", "html_url": "https://github.com/jonas-schievink", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.c